def spike(filename):
    pombe = filename[:-8] + 'pombe.sam'
    return sum([1 for i in open(filename) if i[0]!='@'])
In [2]:
def limado(filename):
    df = pd.read_csv(filename, index_col=0)
    M = df.loc[-50:250].idxmax()
    v, k = [], []

    for i in M.index:
        m = M.loc[i]
        v.append(df.loc[m-50:m+50, i].sum())
        k.append(i)
        
    # finally also make the profile to have it handy
    profile = df.mean(axis=1)
    return pd.DataFrame(v, index=k) / spike(filename), profile

ctrols = ['c1','c2','c3','c4','c5','c6']
treats = ['t1','t2','t3','t4','t5','t6']
columns = ctrols + treats

# Med15
Med15_DMSO = pd.concat([Med15_GC[ctrols], Med15_SM[ctrols]], axis=1)
Med15_3IAA = pd.concat([Med15_GC[treats], Med15_SM[treats]], axis=1)

Med15_DMSO.columns, Med15_3IAA.columns = columns, columns

Med15_DMSO.to_csv('Med15_DMSO_limma.csv')
Med15_3IAA.to_csv('Med15_3IAA_limma.csv')

# Med2_15
Med2_15_DMSO = pd.concat([Med2_15_GC[ctrols], Med2_15_SM[ctrols]], axis=1)
Med2_15_3IAA = pd.concat([Med2_15_GC[treats], Med2_15_SM[treats]], axis=1)

def positives(df): return (set(df[(df['logFC']>np.log(1.5)) & (df['adj.P.Val']<=0.05)].index))
def negatives(df): return (set(df[(df['logFC']<-np.log(1.5)) & (df['adj.P.Val']<=0.05)].index))

pt = positives(_3iaa)
pc = positives(_dmso)
nt = negatives(_3iaa)
nc = negatives(_dmso)

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
import seaborn as sns

inertias=[]
for k in range(2,10):
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=20, max_iter=600).fit(df.values)
    inertias.append(km.inertia_)

plt.figure()
plt.plot(np.arange(2,10), inertias)    
plt.xlabel('clusters'); plt.ylabel('measure of error')

plt.figure(figsize=(18,6))
for n,k in enumerate([2,3,4,5,9]):
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=20, max_iter=600).fit_predict(df.values)
    tmp = df.copy()
    tmp['label'] = km
    tmp['av'] = tmp[df.columns].mean(axis=1)
    tmp = tmp.sort_values(['label','av'], ascending=False).drop(['label', 'av'], axis=1)
    plt.subplot(1,5,n+1)
    cbar = [False if k<9 else True][0]
    ax = sns.heatmap(tmp, cbar=cbar, vmin=-4, vmax=4); plt.title(str(k)+ ' clusters')
    ax.set_yticklabels([])

    peak = start + summit

def assign_peak(chromosome, start, summit):
    peak = start + summit
    potential = SGD[(SGD.chromosome==chromosome) & (peak >= SGD.m) & (peak <= SGD.M)]
    return(list(potential.index))   
    
peaks = []
for i in spt3_macs.index:
    chromosome, start, end = spt3_macs.loc[i,['chromosome','start','summit?']]
    peaks.append(assign_peak(chromosome, start, end))

peaks = list(set(np.hstack(peaks)))
